      "reply_to_tweet_id": null,
      "reply_to_account": null,
      "quoted_tweet_id": null,
      "retweeted_tweet_id": null,
      "text": "🚨 UPDATE: War Powers Resolution vote is scheduled at 4pm ET today. \n\nBarack Obama dropped 26,000 bombs in at least 7 countries in 2016 without a word from Congress. I won’t hamstring President Trump. Unlike many before him, @POTUS is the ‘peace through strength’ President. He has earned our trust just 4.5 days into this mission.\n\nAs Democrat Senator John Fetterman rightfully acknowledged, the President must notify Congress within 48 hours of military action. He did that. If Congress does not declare war, the President must terminate the use of armed forces within 60-90 days.\n\n106 hours into this conflict, President Trump is well within his authority as Commander in Chief. I’ll vote NO on Democrat Tim Kaine’s resolution.",
      "text_resolved": "🚨 UPDATE: War Powers Resolution vote is scheduled at 4pm ET today. \n\nBarack Obama dropped 26,000 bombs in at least 7 countries in 2016 without a word from Congress. I won’t hamstring President Trump. Unlike many before him, @POTUS is the ‘peace through strength’ President. He has earned our trust just 4.5 days into this mission.\n\nAs Democrat Senator John Fetterman rightfully acknowledged, the President must notify Congress within 48 hours of military action. He did that. If Congress does not declare war, the President must terminate the use of armed forces within 60-90 days.\n\n106 hours into this conflict, President Trump is well within his authority as Commander in Chief. I’ll vote NO on Democrat Tim Kaine’s resolution.",
      "lang": "en",
      "hashtags": [],
      "mentions": [
        "POTUS"
      ],
      "urls": [],
